 This Anzac Day Australians took advantage of the opportunity to play the century-old tradition of two-up in pubs and clubs .
The game dates back to Australia 's goldfields and the first recorded games are in the late 1790s .
On Saturday , as Aussies commemorated the landing at Gallipoli , thousands of men and women took their chances with the coin game .
